      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental test conditions must be documented and traceable to clinical operating envelope. Level 3 requires independent measurement uncertainty quantification for all boundary condition inputs including hematocrit, temperature, and inlet velocity profile.",
      "rationale": "In-vitro bench tests conducted using bovine blood at 37 °C with hematocrit 33±2%. Flow rates set by calibrated Coriolis meter (±1.5%). Temperature maintained by recirculating bath. The test protocol follows established FDA pump testing guidance and results are consistent with published literature for this device class. Minor deviations from clinical conditions are considered acceptable given the comparative nature of the RH criterion and the conservative operating points selected."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
